==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1746. From {{der|en|NL.|abdōminālis}}, from {{der|en|la|abdōmen}}.<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=2}}</ref> Equivalent to {{af|en|abdomin-|-al}}. Compare {{cog|fr|abdominal}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/æbˈdɒm.ə.nl̩/|/əbˈdɒm.ə.nl̩/|a=RP}}
* {{IPA|en|/æbˈdɑm.ə.nl̩/|/əbˈdɑm.ə.nl̩/|a=US}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-abdominal.ogg|a=US}}
* {{hyphenation|en|ab|dom|i|nal}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or pertaining to the [[abdomen]]; [[ventral]]. {{defdate|Mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>
#: {{co|en|'''abdominal''' muscles}}
#: {{co|en|'''abdominal''' cavity}}
# {{lb|en|ichthyology}} Having the [[ventral fin]]s under the abdomen and behind the [[pectoral fin]]s. {{defdate|Mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|ichthyology}} [[ventral|Ventral]], in describing a fin. {{defdate|Late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|zoology|obsolete}} Belonging to the order [[Abdominales]] of fish.

